If that isn't part of how we are rethinking the world,

58:12.000 --> 58:16.000
then these technologies are, in fact, not even technologies.

58:16.000 --> 58:19.000
I would agree with that because they're not

58:19.000 --> 58:21.000
being used in this way.

58:21.000 --> 58:26.000
What I'm simply suggesting is that there is a presumption,

58:26.000 --> 58:29.000
and I think, honestly, I think it's one that's rather deep

58:29.000 --> 58:33.000
in a Western liberal individualist framework,

58:33.000 --> 58:38.000
that first there is a cognitive psychological transformation

58:38.000 --> 58:42.000
that then is made manifest upon the world,

58:42.000 --> 58:48.000
that somehow the agency and subjectivity are the same thing,

58:48.000 --> 58:51.000
that our agency in the world is ultimately

58:51.000 --> 58:53.000
a function of our subjectivity.

58:53.000 --> 58:57.000
And what I'm suggesting, honestly, I think I'm making

58:57.000 --> 59:00.000
